    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="177" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received August 21.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>China and Japan were both willing to exempt merchant vessels of the other
                            from seizure, but the negotiations have failed because Japan wished her
                            merchant vessels to continue coming to China, and the Yamên could not
                            revoke imperial order to destroy Japanese ships entering Chinese
                            ports.</p>
            </div>
